<font color="#FF0000">WELCOME, JOHN SIMKIN!</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov  2 14:48:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John,<br><br>
Welcome!<br><br>
Your web site is massive, and reflects a thorough crossection of all aspects of the Vietnam war. I am enjoying exploring it, and will add it to my list of links on my personal Vietnam web page. <br><br>
You and your students will find in the dialog here a contemporary cross section of the issues that continue to plague many Vietnam Veterans, their family and friends, war protestors, children of Vietnam Veterans, and just concerned people.<br><br>
Though the historical accounts of the Vietnam War are fixed in time and space, the emotional, psychological, and political aspects continue for may as if the Vietnam War has not ended. Indeed, it lives on, for better or for worse.<br><br>
There should be no hesitation by you or any of your students to contact Vietnam Veterans active on this dialog site by posting questions, or by e-mail off line. We will do our best to respond and answer your questions. <br><br>
John, thanks for the dignity and honesty of your web site. It is a credit to your efforts in truly educating young people. Perhaps, in some small way, we all can influence the future and prevent the tragedy of another &quot;Vietnam War&quot;.<br><br>
Arthur Varanelli<br>
1/7 ARTY, 1st Infantry Division<br>
2/77 ARTY, 25th Infantry Division<br>
Republic of Vietnam, May 1969 to June, 1970<br><br>
 
